   structure in 258 individuals (171 females and 87 males) from 7
   populations spanning most of its known range. Deviation from
   Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium (F-IS = + 0.254) suggested P. doleritica to
   be inbred, as in many other communal nesting bee species. Global F-ST
